[[!meta date="Sat, 30 Jul 2016 01:02:03 +0000"]]
[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 2.4"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

Several security holes that affect Tails 2.4 are now fixed in Tails 2.5.

We **strongly** encourage you to [[upgrade to Tails 2.5|news/version_2.5]] as soon as possible.

Details
=======

* Tor Browser: [[!mfsa 2016-62]], [[!mfsa 2016-63]], [[!mfsa 2016-64]],
  [[!mfsa 2016-65]], [[!mfsa 2016-67]], [[!mfsa 2016-70]],
  [[!mfsa 2016-72]], [[!mfsa 2016-73]], [[!mfsa 2016-76]],
  [[!mfsa 2016-77]], [[!mfsa 2016-78]], [[!mfsa 2016-79]],
  [[!mfsa 2016-80]]
* Icedove: [[!debsa2016 3601]]
* Linux: [[!debsa2016 3616]], [[!debsa2016 3607]]
* GIMP: [[!debsa2016 3612]]
* libav: [[!debsa2016 3603]]
* expat: [[!debsa2016 3597]]
* libgd3: [[!debsa2016 3630]]
* libmodule-build-perl, perl: [[!debsa2016 3628]]
* Pidgin: [[!debsa2016 3620]] (Tails is not affected since it does
  not include support for the MXit protocol)
* LibreOffice: [[!debsa2016 3608]]
* libxslt1.1: [[!debsa2016 3605]]
* OpenSSH: [[!debsa2016 3626]] (Tails is not affected since it does
  not include the SSH daemon)
* p7zip: [[!debsa2016 3599]]
